Let the (unbiased) estimator of \(\sigma^{2}\) based on a sample of size \(n\) be denoted \(s^{2}\). Then \((n-1)s^{2}/\sigma^{2}\) has a \(\chi^{2}\) distribution with \(\mathrm{df}\ =n-1\). Thus

